1- Basic Express server, dotenv and Git

-Initialize a project called devCamper_api
-touch server.js

2-npm i express dotenv nodemon

--ADD the body parser express middleware

-- go to the package.json and add two scripts:

"start": "NODE_ENV=production node server.js
"dev": "nodemon server.js"

-set up nodemon => start

3-create a config folder and inside config.env file
add:
PORT=5000 
NODE_ENV=development
DB 

-Load the config file
import dotenv at the top
dotenv.config({path: './config/config.env'}) 

4-create a basic express server.

-When console login the app listening:

app.listen(PORT, console.log(`Server running in ${process.env.NODE_ENV} mode on on port${port}`)

5-Initilize git and the gitignore

node_modules
config/config.env

commit and put it github


